ets face it, that's why we play.<br>
<br>
As a result, Mythic HAVE to start playing around with more RvR content, or more and more of the player base will continue to get bored/frustrated and leave.<br>
<br>
DF was a good start, but ultimately, it's already been completed by the hardcore players.<br>
<br>
The Battlegrounds was an excellent idea, fairly well implemented, but its over way too soon (::sniffs:<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Again and again, I hear the argument: &quot;its not PvP - its *R*v*R*&quot; but lately, talk to most of the 45+ crowd, and all RvR seems to be is either small groups looking for action or the Zerg lagfest.<br>
<br>
Perhaps the main problem is that the frontier is too realistic... vast distances meaning everyone converges on a focal point as soon as the skirmishing group vs group gains numbers. Unfortunately, there are few tactics involved (or necessary) in the taking of keeps - as a result, RvR is usually dry, dull or frustrating except for those fun midrange battles.<br>
<br>
Solution? Well, there have been many ideas thrown into the ring by players, but almost all of them involve breaking out of the model for frontier warfare that Mythic has in place.<br>
<br>
Perhaps instead of the most popular idea, a High level battleground, Mythic should create a realm mission feature.<br>
<br>
Based around the players in a chatgroup i.e. max of 30 people, the portal would take you to a random zone map (Not randomly generated on the fly, but a pregenerated map) and the players would have to complete a mission. Capture an artifact from a keep, destroy a bridge, assassinate a noble etc.<br>
<br>
These zones would have a number of checkpoint milegates which would be opened either by siege, or by completing a mission goal. This would create a number of subzones which could randomly add Realm Guards, and Mobs to adjust the challenge of the mission dependant on the levels of the players on the mission, and the amount of defenders. So, 30 players, all high level, higher level mobs and realm guards, and more mobs and guards. More defenders, slower spawn rate of guards etc.<br>
<br>
Mythic could have fun with this by maybe having a contest for player designed mission zones.<br>
<br>
I would picture the scenario as follows. The CG Leader &quot;purchases&quot; the mission with KPs (I'll explain these at the end - bear with me) from the Captain of the guard in the Portal Keep. All other players wishing to go also purchase a mission medallion (For a reduced amount of KPs) The leader then uses a CG command to synchronise everyone in the group's medallion with the same destination. Shift-I on the medallion will give the information of the mission. <br>
<br>
The players portal in as normal to a spawned mission zone. <br>
<br>
On the opposing side, Players can purchase Realm Defense mission medallions (also at a reduced rate of KPs) and port to where they are needed. (With a maximum of 30 defenders going to that newly created zone)<br>
<br>
If there are no Enemy missions currently in action, defenders would portal in as normal, and be able to xp off some of the mobs near the mission objective area.<br>
<br>
There should be a mission timer of 3 hours that starts as soon as the attacking realm portals in. With the mission objective being completeable (not sure if it is a word) no less than 90 mins. Thus, each mission would not require a power gaming schedule to play. Also once that timer has started, players who have died and left the zone can return by talking to the Captain of the guard. (Cause making people wait on a return port and then catching up will be hard enough as it is)<br>
<br>
If the player logs off or goes LD, their Medallion loses the mission key until the CG leader flashes them again with a CG command. Mission key medallions can be traded with other players if replacements are needed.<br>
<br>
On completion of the mission, the group heads back to the mission portal (again, within that 3 hour timer) and the original CG leader speaks to the Agent in the mission zone to complete the mission (like a quest) all the medallions of live people in the zone are then flashed as completed, and become untradeable.(To prevent twinking)<br>
<br>
If it fails, all defense medallions in the zone (whether the defender owning it is alive or dead) are flashed as successful defense, and become untradeable.<br>
<br>
The reward for completing a mission would be a fixed amount of Realm Points reward, some experience, and items. Each member would hand in their mission medallion for that reward, and the raid leaders medallion would give the items in addition. (Chat Group would reveal the items granted to the leader)<br>
<br>
The same rewards would be given to defenders for succcessfully defending against a mission. (Minus the item reward)<br>
<br>
Ok... so what are KPs - these would be Keep Points. (I'm sure someone can figure out a better name) and would be granted for killing a Keep Lord. To qualify for Keep Points, you or your groupmates would normally qualify for experience if the keep lord was a regular mob. If there was anyway to award that by range, and not dead or alive status, I would strongly recommend that.(Tho I dont know if Mythic can add that in without severly messing with the xp code <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
The Amount of KPs would be based on the keep value, and then modified by the amount of opposing players defending the keep. (Again, not sure how that could be coded - but it would reward players for difficult sieges). <br>
<br>
This would continue the war in the frontier, and make sure that plenty of variety would be available to the players.<br>
It would also allow mythic to play around with new ideas to make RvR encounters more enjoyable for Melee types (as tanks will be an absolute necessity to complete the mission) <br>
<br>
It would also be fun for us rogues <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
