 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaiyasamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maiya Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/28/02 9:32:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2983.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> It's not just RvR...</span><hr size=1> Contrary to popular belief, the endgame isn't all about RvR. Everyone I've met who played to 50 and RvR'd their way to the top 25 in realm points have left the game. I guess they "won" and then proceeded to leave the game out of boredom or sold their characters.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, the sub-50 people I know who don't RvR much and have been playing since day 2 (because I don't know anyone who actually managed to get Camelot on release day) spend a great deal of time doing PvE stuff: Hunting in the epic zone, darkness falls, tradeskills, etc.<br>
<br>
Last I heard, no one has killed one of the epic zone dragons yet. Most people consider the feat impossible. I remember another game where people had the same opinion about dragons.<br>
<br>
The problem with any content, RvR or PvE is that players will devour it faster than Mythic can create it. Good content takes time to build and only moments to explore and conquer.<br>
<br>
Your suggestions for realm missions are extremely difficult to code. The whole concept of realm points, bounty points, and realm levels is confusing enough for the average player. Mythic probably doesn't want to confuse people any further.<br>
<br>
Some of the PvP additions Mythic really needs to add includes:<br>
<br>
A dueling arena, where players from all three realms can compete one on one against each other with no realm point exchange.<br>
<br>
Making keeps harder to take, because as it stand now Midgard and Albion can take a keep on Percival in 5 minutes without seige gear. How to make it harder? Doors should require siege gear to break them. Archers on the walls should get flaming arrows to attack siege gear and concentrate on attacking siege gear. You'll then need assassins to take out the archers and crafters to build seige gear in order to take a keep. No more of this Zergling rush to take Dun Crauchon and die at Dun Crimthainn to get into Darkness Falls.<br>
<br>
A better informational system for knowing when a keep is under seige. It's very difficult to defend keeps without having someone stationed at each keep watching. This leads to people having twinks waiting in the keeps for would-be attackers. Some early warning system such as when the keep is under attack Rank 2 and up players get messages stating such.<br>
<br>
Extra RPs for defending. If you're in the "zone" area of a keep your realm controls and kill an attacker, you get 25% bonus RPs. There's a real problem with getting people to defend keeps because they want phat RPs. Well, give them some added incentive to stay near the keep and defend from attackers.<br>
<br>
With Darkness Falls, there's a real incentive for people to get involved with RvR. More incentives such as Darkness Falls would be great. I leave this open because Mythic seems to have some creative talent that comes up with these ideas regularly.<br>
<br>
All said, I really don't think the system is that broken. More incentives are needed to do things such as defend, and assemble a real keep siege force. It's all too simple right now. But with the proper incentives in place, RvR will require a bit more planning and call upon the unique skills of everyone involved.<br>
