<br>
This is exactly the point of this idea. To counter the ennui, and to make 45-50 fun.<br>
<br>
The end game consists RvR, Getting loot from DF and your 50th Epic quest, and playing with the Dragon. After your first 50 deaths, you'll probably get bored/frustrated with the Dragon, you'll eventually (and fairly quickly) get the equipment you want. all that's left is the RvR (as it's the only content in DAoC that is constantly changing)<br>
<br>
The whole point of this suggestion is to add something more fun, and that will stimulate the war in the frontier. (DF is very nice, but most of the 50's I know have &quot;done it&quot; already) <br>
<br>
The main draw of this game is the RvR system, the battlegrounds were a great shot in the arm, and although I think they need one from 36-40 (RRank 2.5 cap) and possibly one for 41-45 (RRank 3.0 cap) having a battleground for the 46+ folks would kill the original frontier (not a bad thing, I just don't think Mythic would go for it)<br>
<br>
As far as this being difficult to code, Mythic has most of the tools in place already to create these mission zones. The idea is essentially based on the existing engine (Quests, Items, Porting) The only thing that isn't in the game is the ability to open Milegates on completion of a mission sub goal. (And I don't believe that would be all that hard)<br>
<br>
Also, the addition of one more Point Currency, I do not believe will confuse the players who are able to participate in these missions.<br>
<br>
Saiya: &quot;The problem with any content, RvR or PvE is that players will devour it faster than Mythic can create it. Good content takes time to build and only moments to explore and conquer.&quot;<br>
<br>
Exactly, no mission would be exactly alike (different attackers, defenders create a huge number of variables) thus your content is always changing.<br>
<br>
Saiya: &quot;Some of the PvP additions Mythic really needs to add includes:<br>
<br>
A dueling arena, where players from all three realms can compete one on one against each other with no realm point exchange.&quot;<br>
<br>
This would be fun, but what would it accomplish?<br>
<br>
&quot;A better informational system for knowing when a keep is under seige. It's very difficult to defend keeps without having someone stationed at each keep watching. This leads to people having twinks waiting in the keeps for would-be attackers. Some early warning system such as when the keep is under attack Rank 2 and up players get messages stating such&quot;<br>
<br>
Absolutely, I saw a great post at the vault network dev board regarding this, I'll repost/post the link if anyone requests it, but essentially it was about making keeps work as a &quot;radar&quot; network for informing players where the enemy was and what numbers they had.<br>
<br>
&quot;Extra RPs for defending. If you're in the &quot;zone&quot; area of a keep your realm controls and kill an attacker, you get 25% bonus RPs. There's a real problem with getting people to defend keeps because they want phat RPs. Well, give them some added incentive to stay near the keep and defend from attackers.&quot; <br>
